@lesssugaronly Dear Customer,
Thank you for choosing Korean Air.
In principle, baggage connection is not possible on separate tickets, but it may be possible depending on the airport situation or flight route. So please check once more when you check in at the airport.

@paddy_ptp Hi,

Regarding in-flight entertainment program, please check our SKY Program list.

https://t.co/mffbSWA5R7

@RafalEstates If the traveler wishes to leave the airport during transit time, the traveler should check if the country requires visas. 
The K-ETA visa is required for entry to South Korea, you can find more information on our Travel Regulation Map. 

https://t.co/l2PCUldCG5.

@tipekusair Hello, thank you for choosing Korean Air. 
For more information about baggage allowance including fishing equipments, please visit Korean Air's website

https://t.co/upxOTmYSZb

@garydolman Dear Gary,
With regard to lost baggage, it is the rule that the last airline you boarded handles the request.
If the last flight you boarded on your journey was Korean Air, please fill in the details on the customer feedback page.

@khunhappy We are regret for your inconvenience, again.

Also If you would like to receive an official answer, please visit 'Customer feedback' page and fill out necessary information so that the relevant department can review it.

Customer feedback page : https://t.co/reN2siPKtW

@khunhappy Dear customer, thank you for choosing Korean Air. 

Kindly contact our service center or chatbot livechat, where can assist your inquiries. 
(If your reservation is created by travel agency, please contact them directly.)

@garydolman Dear Gary Dolman.

We are regret for your inconvenience.
If you reported to the Korean Air staff at the local airport, they would be in the process of retrieving the bag.

